text: Valromey-sur-Séran is a new commune in the Ain department of eastern France. It was founded on 1 January 2019. It is made of the former communes of Belmont-Luthézieu, Lompnieu, Sutrieu and Vieu.Arrêté préfectoral , 17 December 2018 == References == Category:2019 establishments in France Category:Communes in Ain
title: Valromey-sur-Séran
